Implicit variable
- Implicit variable values are set at application context level.

Implicit in variable in method
- If no parameter/value is passed to a method, then the compiler will look for implicit value in application cotext and pass it as the parameter.

NOTE:
- A method can only contain one implicit keyword.
- With CURRYING we can prevent all params becoming implicit
- implicit parameter have to define at end like func3()

E.g. Some samples:
def func1(implicit x : Int)             // x is implicit
def func2(implicit x : Int, y : Int)    // x and y both are implicit ************
def func3 (x : Int)(implicit y : Int)   // only y is implicit *********

E.g -1

implicit val a=10
val b=2

def addition (param1 : Int)(implicit param2 : Int) = {
  println(param1)
  println(param2)
  param1 + param2
}
println(addition(b))

----Outcome---
2
10
12



